A prototype (Fig. 6
) was developed to implement the proposed RSMO model. All the functions store, manage and analyze relative space data were encoded into a dynamic link library within C++ environment. The visualization of this prototype was developed by the QGIS (Quantum GIS) framework in a Python environment. Two typical analysis modules were implemented, namely, query processing and relative relationship dynamic pattern transformation. The query processing contained all six operators (Point extraction, Time drilling, Target drilling, Time curvilinear drilling, Time cutting and Target cutting
). Two relative relationship dynamic pattern matching algorithms (accompaniments and trackers) were implemented in this prototype.
